commit.message: allow octal numbers
Bump version to 0.0.7.

Treat strict mode future reserved words as identifiers.

As RKelly doesn't differenciate between strict mode and non-strict mode,
always allow these future reserved words which otherwise should be not
allowed in strict mode.

Added tests to cover parsing of reserved words.
Bump version to 0.0.6.

Handle Unicode whitespace characters.

Unfortunately JavaScript allows any Unicode "space separator"
chars to be part of whitespace, so we need to pull off some
trickery to support all these chars in both Ruby 1.9+ (easy, as
it has Unicode support) and in 1.8 (fall back to byte-processing).
Bump version to 0.0.5.

Add install instructions to README.

And fix links too.
Typo in README.

Document the methods of Node class.

These are really the actual API of RKelly, but completely undocumented.

Fix tests for parsing 0x0 and 0X0.

Previously the generated tests had three tests for converting "0",
which also resulted in warning of 'method test_num_0 redefined',
now there are separate tests for "0", "0x0", "0X0".
Describe the benefits of RKelly Remix fork in README.
Merge branch 'reserved-words'
Merge branch 'ecma-visitor-fix'

Update list of reserved words to match ECMAScript 5.

ES5 removed a bunch of reserved words that ES3 had reserved.  These
are also supported as identifiers by real-world implementations. So
removing these.

ES5 added 'let' and 'yield' to the reserved list, which have been added
in here too.

Fix ecma visitor for function expressions with name.

Make the Getter and Setter visitors also handle the visiting of the
related FunctionExprNode, not rely on the visit_FunctionExprNode, which
can accordingly be changed to also include "function" before its name.

To DRY things up, move the common bit of all the Function-visiting
methods to #function_params_and_body helper method.

Also add a test case.
Bump version to 0.0.4.

Allow use of keywords in property names.

According to ECMAScript 5.1, this is allowed:

    x = {var: 10};
    x.var = 7;

So I introduced a new rule IdentName that encompasses identifiers,
keywords and reserved words, which are all allowed to be used as
property names.

Remove ENUM from keyword tokens list.

It's a future reserved word, not a full-blown keyword.
Bump version to 0.0.3.
Write changelog for the latest versions.

Add RKelly::Parser#stopped_at method.

Useful for error reporting.
Bump version to 0.0.2.

Simplify :S token regex.

Ruby 1.9 printed a warning for the old regex.

Using just \s is enough to match all whitespace.

Handle multibyte chars in Tokenizer.

Previously the tokenizer crashed in Ruby 1.9 when unicode characters
present in input, because the scan pointer was advanced by string
length, which in Ruby 1.8 is the length in bytes, but in 1.9 is
the length of chars.

Now using #bytesize method in Ruby 1.9+.

Fork RKelly as "RKelly Remix".

We'll start version numbers from 0.0.1.

The gem is named rkelly-remix, while the library will remain name-
spaced under RKelly - so using both rkelly and rkelly-remix will cause
a conflict.
Remove trailing whitespace in tokenizer test.

Allow unescaped slash '/' inside regex [charset].

Previously this valid regex wasn't recognized:

    /[/]/
